      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHISKY POINT (2) goes very well here starting seven times for three wins and two minors. Hit the frame latest (22.75) when second at Geelong in a Grade 5. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. GENESIS BALE (3) finished third (23.77) two back at this track but out of the placings last time when 6th there. Solid record here at the distance winning four races. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and four minor placings to his credit. Can measure up this time. GRAVITY RUSH (8) drew the inside and won last time at Warragul over 460m (26.52), scoring by 1.5 lengths. Bold showing expected again. ORSON FURY (5) is very honest and looms as a strong top-three hope again.",
